1. **Identify knowns and unknowns:**
   n = 0.50 mol
   P = 2.0 × 10⁵ Pa
   T_C = 27 °C
   R = 8.31 J mol⁻¹ K⁻¹
   V = ?

2. **Convert temperature to Kelvin:**
   T_K = T_C + 273 = 27 + 273 = 300 K

3. **Select and rearrange the Ideal Gas Equation (PV = nRT) to solve for V:**
   V = \frac{nRT}{P}

4. **Substitute values and calculate:**
   V = \frac{(0.50 \text{ mol}) \times (8.31 \text{ J mol⁻¹ K⁻¹}) \times (300 \text{ K})}{2.0 \times 10⁵ \text{ Pa}}
   V = \frac{1246.5}{2.0 \times 10⁵}
   V = 0.0062325 \text{ m³}

5. **State the final answer with appropriate significant figures:**
   V = 6.2 × 10⁻³ \text{ m³}
